10.3 DML Inference in the Interactive Regression Model

DML Inference on APEs and ATEs

interactive regression model (IRM) propensity score 2

\[\begin{align} Y & = g_0(D, X) + \varepsilon, \quad \mathbb{E}[\varepsilon | X, D] = 0, \tag{10.3.1} \\ D & = m_0(X) + \tilde{D}, \quad \mathbb{E}[\tilde{D} | X] = 0. \tag{10.3.2} \end{align}\]

  • \(W=(Y,D,X)\)
    • \(Y\)
    • \(D\in\{0,1\}\) (binary treatment variable)
    • \(X\) (controls/confounding factors)
  • \((10.2.1)\) (PLM)
    • \((10.3.1)\)\(D\) \(X\) (additive separable) \(X\) (treatment effect)
    • \((10.3.2)\)\(D\) \(X\) \(D\) \(X\) (confounded)
  • \(g_0\) \(m_0\)

(parameter of interest): (APE)

\[\begin{equation} \theta_0 = \mathbb{E}[g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X)] \tag{10.3.3} \end{equation}\]

  • \(D \perp Y(d) \mid X\) ( ignorability / ignorability) APE (ATE)

Neyman

  • \(g_0\) \(m_0\) \(\theta_0\) \(\varphi_0(W)\)

\[\begin{equation} \theta_0 = \mathbb{E}[\varphi_0(W)], \tag{10.3.4} \end{equation}\]

  • \(\varphi_0(W)\)

\[\begin{equation} \varphi_0(W) = \varphi_0(Y,D,X) = g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X) + (Y - g_0(D, X))H_0, \end{equation}\]

  • \(H_0\) Horvitz-Thompson weight \[\begin{equation} H_0 = \frac{1(D = 1)}{m_0(X)} - \frac{1(D = 0)}{1 - m_0(X)}. \end{equation}\]

  • : doubly robust

    • \(g_0\) \(m_0\) \(\theta\)

Remark 10.3.1: Regression Adjustment or Propensity ScoreReweighting? Use both

  • (Regression adjustment)

\[\begin{equation} \theta_0=\mathrm{E}\left[g_0(1, X)-g_0(0, X)\right], \end{equation}\]

  • (Propensity Score Reweighting)

\[\begin{equation} \theta_0=\mathrm{E}\left[Y H_0\right] . \end{equation}\]

  • 2 Neyman Orthogonality

: DML for APEs/ATEs

  1. Cross-fitting

    • \(\{I_k\}_{k=1}^K\) fold \(K\)
    • \(k\) \(g_0\) \(m_0\) \(m_{[k]}\) \(g_{[k]}\)
    • fold \(i \in I_k\)

    \[\begin{equation} \hat{\varphi}(W_i) = \hat{g}_{[k]}(1, X_i) - \hat{g}_{[k]}(0, X_i) + (Y_i - \hat{g}_{[k]}(D_i, X_i))\hat{H}_i, \end{equation}\] : \[\begin{equation} \hat{H}_i = \frac{1(D_i = 1)}{\hat{m}_{[k]}(X_i)} - \frac{1(D_i = 0)}{1 - \hat{m}_{[k]}(X_i)}. \end{equation}\]

  2. \(\theta\) \[\begin{equation} \hat{\theta} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^n \hat{\varphi}(W_i). \end{equation}\]

    • \[\begin{equation} \hat{V} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^n (\hat{\varphi}(W_i) - \hat{\theta})^2. \end{equation}\]
    • \[\begin{equation} \text{Std. Error} = \sqrt{\frac{\hat{V}}{n}}. \end{equation}\]

Remark 10.3.2: Trimming

  • \(m_{[k]}\) 0 1 \((|\hat{H}_i|)\)
    • overlap
  • (trimming)
    • (\(\varepsilon = 0.01\)) \(\bar{H} = 100\)
    • trimming

Theorem 10.3.1: Adaptive Inference on ATE with DML

    • Overlap (\(\varepsilon < m_0(X) < 1 - \varepsilon\))
    • \(g_0, m_0\) \[\begin{equation} \left\|\hat{g}_{[k]}-g_0\right\|_{L^2}+\left\|\hat{m}_{[k]}-m_0\right\|_{L^2}+\sqrt{n}\left\|_{\delta[k]}-g_0\right\|_{L^2}\left\|\hat{m}_{[k]}-m_0\right\|_{L^2} \approx 0, \end{equation}\]

  • (nuisance parameter) \(\hat{\theta}\) \[\begin{equation} \sqrt{n}\left(\hat{\theta}-\theta_0\right) \approx \sqrt{n} \mathbb{E}_n\left[\varphi_0(W)-\theta_0\right] . \end{equation}\]

  • \(\sqrt{n}\) \[\begin{equation} \sqrt{n}(\hat{\theta} - \theta_0) \approx \mathcal{N}(0, V), \end{equation}\] \[\begin{equation} V = \mathbb{E}[(\varphi_0(W) - \theta_0)^2]. \end{equation}\]

  • \(g_0\) \(m_0\)

DML Inference for GATEs and ATETs

GATEs (Group Average Treatment Effects)

  • (GATE) \[\begin{equation} \theta_0 = \mathbb{E}[g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X) \mid G = 1] \end{equation}\]

  • :

    • \(G = 1\) 1319 (\(13 \leq \text{Age} \leq 19\))
    • \(G = 1\) \(65 \leq \text{Age}\)

  • \[\begin{equation} \theta_0=\mathrm{E}\left[\varphi_0(X) \mid G=1\right]=\mathrm{E}\left[\varphi_0(X) G\right] / \mathrm{P}(G=1) . \end{equation}\]

ATET (Average Treatment Effect on the Treated)

\[\begin{equation} \theta_0 = \mathbb{E}[g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X) \mid D = 1] \end{equation}\]

Remark 10.3.3: Misspecification of PLM as inference on an overlap-weighted APE

  • PLM PLM \(\beta\)
  • IRM \(\tilde{Y}\) \(\tilde{D}\) BLP (best linear predictor) \[\begin{equation} g_0(D, X) = g_0(0, X) + D(g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X)) \end{equation}\]
    • IRM\(Y\) \(D\)
    • \(g_0(0,X)\) PLM \(\ell(X)\)
  • \(\tilde{Y}\)

\[\begin{equation} \tilde{Y}=\tilde{D}\left(g_0(1, X)-g_0(0, X)\right)+\epsilon . \end{equation}\]

  • Theorem 10.2.1 (10.2.3) \(\beta\)

\[\begin{equation} \beta:=\{b: E[(\tilde{Y}-b \tilde{D}) \tilde{D}]=0\}=\left(\mathrm{E}\left[\tilde{D}^2\right]\right)^{-1} \mathrm{E}[\tilde{D} \tilde{Y}], \end{equation}\]

  • \(\mathrm{E}\left[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X\right]=m_0(X)\left(1-m_0(X)\right)\) \(\beta\) \(m_0(X)\) \(g_0(X)\)

\[\begin{align} &\beta = \frac{\mathrm{E}[\tilde{D} \tilde{Y}]}{\mathrm{E}\left[\tilde{D}^2\right]} \\ \Rightarrow &\beta = \frac{\mathrm{E}[\tilde{D} \left\{\tilde{D}\left(g_0(1, X)-g_0(0, X)\right)+\epsilon\right\}]}{\mathrm{E}\left[m_0(X)\left(1-m_0(X)\right)\right]} \quad \because \text{$\tilde{Y}$ } \\ \Rightarrow &\beta = \frac{\mathrm{E}[\tilde{D}^2\left(g_0(1, X)-g_0(0, X)\right)]}{\mathrm{E}\left[m_0(X)\left(1-m_0(X)\right)\right]} + \frac{\mathrm{E}[\tilde{D} \epsilon]}{\mathrm{E}\left[m_0(X)\left(1-m_0(X)\right)\right]} \\ \therefore ~ &\beta = \frac{\mathbb{E}[m_0(X)(1 - m_0(X))(g_0(1, X) - g_0(0, X))]}{\mathbb{E}[m_0(X)(1 - m_0(X))]} \end{align}\]

  • \(m_0(X) \approx 1/2\) \(m_0(X) \approx 0\) \(m_0(X) \approx 1\)
    • :

: \(\mathrm{E}\left[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X\right]=m_0(X)\left(1-m_0(X)\right)\)

  • (10.3.2) \(\tilde{D}\) \[\begin{align} &D = m_0(X) + \tilde{D}, \quad \mathbb{E}[\tilde{D} | X] = 0 \\ \tag{10.3.2} \Rightarrow & \tilde{D} = D - m_0(X) \end{align}\]

  • \(\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X]\) \[\begin{align} &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = \mathbb{E}[(D - m_0(X))^2 \mid X] \\ \Rightarrow &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = \mathbb{E}[D^2 \mid X] - 2m_0(X)\mathbb{E}[D \mid X] + m_0(X)^2 \end{align}\]

  • \(D \in \{0, 1\}\) \(D^2 = D\) \(\mathbb{E}[D \mid X] = m_0(X)\) \[\begin{align} &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = \mathbb{E}[D \mid X] - 2m_0(X)m_0(X) + m_0(X)^2 \\ \Rightarrow &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = m_0(X) - 2m_0(X)^2 + m_0(X)^2 \\ \Rightarrow &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = m_0(X) - m_0(X)^2 \\ \because ~ &\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D}^2 \mid X] = m_0(X)(1 - m_0(X)). \end{align}\]

Remark 10.3.3:

  • \(D \in [0, 1]\) \(g_0(D, X)\) + \(D\) \[\begin{equation} g_0(D, X) = g_0(0, X) + \int_0^D t \cdot g_0'(t, X) dt \end{equation}\]

  • \(\beta\) weighted average derivative \[\begin{equation} \beta = \frac{\mathbb{E}[w(D, X) g_0'(D, X)]}{\mathbb{E}[w(D, X)]} \end{equation}\] \(w(D, X)\) \[\begin{equation} w(D, X) = \frac{\mathbb{E}[\tilde{D} \mid D > d, X]}{f(D \mid X)} \end{equation}\]

  • binary continuous
